raw_data.title: Configuration Manager
raw_data.description:
A top-performing software developer with experience in technology and IT support. A successful team leader capable of supervising the creation and maintenance of servers, office networks, and custom software applications. Skilled in diverse areas and adept at troubleshooting and finding creative solutions while maintaining client and vendor satisfaction. 
Areas of Expertise ▪ Jenkins automation ▪ Jira, Bitbucket automation ▪ Amazon Web Services ▪ Terraform ▪ Linux & Windows OS ▪ Java, Javascript, PHP & HTML ▪ Python, Groovy ▪ MySQL, Postgres & Apache ▪ Virtual Servers & Web Applications ▪ Troubleshooting & Creative Solutions ▪ IT Support & Testing ▪ Client Relations & Support

raw_data.title: Software Developer Sr.
raw_data.description:
The Software Developer (SR) oversees software development projects, writes clean and efficient code, and provides technical leadership to the team. They are responsible for ensuring the quality and functionality of software solutions.
The team uses several different technologies in our development stack across multiple clients and projects. We continuously evaluate new technologies to make sure we are fully aware and always using the right tool for the job.

raw_data.title: Sr. Functional Lead
raw_data.description: Experience in requirement development for applications, experiences, websites, products and services that balance use needs, business objective and technological constraints.  Experience producing client-acing deliverables and presentations and participating in client meetings. Strong analytical and problem solving skills.  Experience gathering requirements remotely, working in a fully remove setting, and working with cross-functional teams.  Strong understanding of Agile software development processes, and waterfall methodologies.  knowledge of design thinking and user experience is a plus. Able to function, adapt and succeed in a constantly changing, fast-paced environment.  Positive attitude and motivation to deliver highest quality work.  Strong communication skills (both verbal and written).  Self-organized and structured, with the ability to define your own tasks.  Experience with MS Office Suite (Word, Excel, and PowerPoint) and G Suite.  Familiarity with JIRA, Confluence, and Slack.

raw_data.title: QA Tester Mid
raw_data.description:
Direct experience with testing systems
Be able to collaborate with developers, business analysts, and UX resources to design manual and automated test cases that have clearly understood entry and success criteria.
Identify, record, document thoroughly and track bugs
Perform thorough regression testing when bugs are resolved
Worked as part of an agile or scrum team and participation in key daily / weekly scrum ceremonies working with issue tracking tools (ex. JIRA/Confluence)
Be familiar with the principles behind cross-browser / cross form-factor testing of web applications.
Have success working with and testing responsive web applications on multiple devices.
Familiar with API testing and experience executing SQL queries
